      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A high-pitched squeal when braking on a Camry, right after a brake pad replacement, is usually a sign that something is rubbing or something is loose. You should first check the caliper and the pads themselves, as a poorly seated pad or a sticking caliper is a common culprit. If you don't find anything obvious, you might need to look at the hardware.",
