    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i checked the pads and they look seated okay, but when i was looking at the caliper it seemed like it might be sticking a bit. the squeal is really consistent though, even a light touch on the pedal makes it happen. could it be the wear indicator sensor or is there something else that causes that specific high pitch?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A sticking caliper, even a little bit, is a prime suspect, and you're right to focus there. If the squeal is consistent and happens with light pedal pressure, it often points to the caliper piston not fully retracting or the slide pins being seized up. It's less likely to be the wear indicator sensor causing a *high-pitched* squeal, though a sensor can certainly throw off the system, making the brake system think something is wrong.",
      "source": "target",
